definition.value: An omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is trans-undec-2-enoic acid in which one of the hydrogens attached to the terminal methyl group is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A 4-O-(1H-indol-3-ylcarbonyl)ascaroside derived from 11-hydroxyundecanoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
A member of the class of naphthoic acids that is 1-naphthoic acid substituted at positions 2, 5 and 7 by hydroxy, methyl and methoxy groups respectively.
An omega-hydroxy fatty acid that is undecanoic acid in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal methyl group is replaced by a hydroxy group.
An ascaroside of a hydroxy fatty acid in which the hydroxy group at position 4 of the ascarylopyranose moiety has been has been converted into the corresponding (E)-2-methyl-2-butenoate ester.
A 4-O-[(E)-2-methyl-2-butenoyl]ascaroside derived from (2E,8R)-8-hydroxynon-2-enoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
A 4-O-[(E)-2-methyl-2-butenoyl]ascaroside derived from (8R)-8-hydroxynonanoic acid. It is a metabolite of the nematode Caenorhabditis elegans.
